VHF Communication Transceiver - Functional Test

ATA Chapter: 23 — Communications
S1000D DMC (Illustrative): B777-A-23-12-11-00-750A-A01A-P


This task involves:

    - Powering up the selected VHF Communication system.
    - Performing Built-In Test Equipment (BITE) check of the VHF Transceiver.
    - Verifying control panel indications and operation.
    - Conducting a transmit and receive check on specified test frequencies using a Ramp Test Set.
    - Confirming audio clarity and signal strength indications.
    - Verifying communication with Air Traffic Control (ATC) via ground communications (if permitted and coordinated).
    - Recording test results.


